​
        <p class='static-page__text static-page__text--sinai'>The following sources were also consulted in creating the descriptive metadata for the manuscripts published through the Sinai Manuscripts Digital Library website.</p>
​
        <p class='static-page__text static-page__text--sinai'>Binggeli = Binggeli, Andr&eacute;. &quot;Les trois David copistes arabes de Palestine aux 9e-10e s.&rdquo; In <i>Manuscripta graeca et orientalia: M&eacute;langes monastiques et patristiques en l&rsquo;honneur de Paul G&eacute;hin</i>. Edited by Andr&eacute; Binggeli, Anne Boud&#39;hors, and Matthieu Cassin, 79-118. Leuven: Peeters, 2016.</p>
​
        <p class='static-page__text static-page__text--sinai'>Brock 2003 = Brock, S. &ldquo;Syriac on Sinai: The Main Connections.&rdquo; In <i>Eukosmia: Studi miscellanei per il 75&deg; di Vincenzo Poggi S.J</i>. Edited by V. Ruggieri and L. Pieralli, 103-117. Catanzaro, 2003.</p>
​
        <p class='static-page__text static-page__text--sinai'>Brock 2011 = Brock, Sebastian P. &quot;The Syriac &#39;New Finds&#39; at St Catherine&#39;s Monastery, Sinai, and Their Significance.&quot; <i>The Harp</i> 27 (2011): 39-52.</p>
​
        <p class='static-page__text static-page__text--sinai'>Brock 2012 = Brock, S. P. &ldquo;Sinai: A Meeting Point of Georgian with Syriac and Christian Palestinian Aramaic.&rdquo; In <i>Caucasus: Between East and West. Historical and Philological Studies in Honour of Zaza Aleksidze</i>, 482-494. Tbilisi: National Centre of Manuscripts, 2012.</p>
​
        <p class='static-page__text static-page__text--sinai'>Froyshov = Froyshov, S. R. &ldquo;L&rsquo;horloge &#39;g&eacute;orgien&#39; du Sinaiticus ibericus 34.&rdquo; PhD diss., Paris IV-Sorbonne, 2003.</p>
​
        <p class='static-page__text static-page__text--sinai'>Kashouh 2008 = Kashouh, Hikmat. &ldquo;Sinai Ar. N.F. Parchment 8 and 28: Its Contribution to Textual Criticism of the Gospel of Luke.&rdquo; <i>Novum Testamentum</i> 50 (2008): 28-57.</p>
​
        <p class='static-page__text static-page__text--sinai'>Kashouh 2012 = Kashouh, Hikmat. <i>The Arabic Versions of the Gospels: The Manuscripts and their Families</i>. Berlin: De Gruyter, 2012. [<%= link_to 'WorldCat', 'https://www.worldcat.org/title/671466151', class: 'si-link' %>]</p>
​
        <p class='static-page__text static-page__text--sinai'>Lamoreaux = Lamoreaux, J.C., ed. <i>The Life of Stephen of Mar Sabas</i>. Leuven: Peeters, 1999. [<%= link_to 'WorldCat', 'https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/42432167', class: 'si-link' %>]</p>
​
        <p class='static-page__text static-page__text--sinai'>Metreveli = Metreveli, E. <i>Dzlisp&#39;irni da &#289;mrtism&scaron;oblisani</i>. Tbilisi, 1971. [<%= link_to 'WorldCat', 'https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/68159930', class: 'si-link' %>]</p>
​
        <p class='static-page__text static-page__text--sinai'>Miklas 2000 = Miklas, H. &ldquo;Zur editorischen Vorbereitung des sog. Missale Sinaiticum (Sin. slav. 5/N).&rdquo; In <i>Glagolitica: Zum Ursprung der slavischen Schriftkultur</i>. Edited by H. Miklas, Sylvia Richter, and Veliza Sadovski, 117-129. Wien: Verlag der &Ouml;sterreichischen Akademie der Wissenschaften, 2000.</p>
​
        <p class='static-page__text static-page__text--sinai'>Miklas, et al. = Miklas, H., et al. <i>Psalterium Demetrii Sinaitici (monasterii sanctae Catharinae codex slav. 3/N)</i>. Glagolitica Sinaitica 1. Vienna, 2012. [<%= link_to 'WorldCat', 'https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/824728170', class: 'si-link' %>]</p>
​
        <p class='static-page__text static-page__text--sinai'>Rossetto = Rossetto, G. <i>Greek Palimpsests at Saint Catherine&rsquo;s Monastery (Sinai): Three Euchologia as Case Studies</i>. Ver&ouml;ffentlichungen zur Byzanzforschung 44. Wien: Austrian Academy of Sciences Press, 2023. [<%= link_to 'WorldCat', 'https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/1370165262', class: 'si-link' %>]</p>
​
        <p class='static-page__text static-page__text--sinai'>SIBE = Gippert, J., W. Schulze, Z. Aleksidze, and J.-P. Mah&eacute;, eds. <i>The Caucasian Albanian Palimpsests of Mount Sinai</i>. Monumenta Palaeographica Medii Aevi: Series Ibero-Caucasica 2. Turnhout, 2008. [<%= link_to 'WorldCat', 'https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/319126785', class: 'si-link' %>]</p>
​
        <p class='static-page__text static-page__text--sinai'>Treiger = Treiger, Alexander. &ldquo;Christian Graeco-Arabica: Prolegomena to a History of the Arabic Translations of the Greek Fathers.&rdquo; In <i>Intellectual History of the Islamicate World</i>, 3:188-227. Leiden: Brill, 2015.</p>
